Reviewer #3: The manuscript by Kim and collaborators is an experimental and numerical characterization of an experimental setup based on a Paul trap for two-dimensional ion crystals. I here give my feedback as a theoretician: I find the manuscript sound, the results very interesting, and their setup is very promising for simulating topological physics with ions. I recommend publication after the authors have considered the following minor remarks:\
\
1. There are some references which are not properly compiled in the manuscript (they appear with ??). \
\
2. The abstract would need some revision in order to make it easier to read.\
\
3. Section IV. \
The authors refer to the aspect ratio needed in order to have a stable planar crystal. The condition is based on mean-field calculations, which assume T=0 and discards quantum fluctuations. I remark that at temperature different from zero the condition is modified. This has been reported in\
D. Podolsky et al, Phys. Rev. X 6, 031025 - Published 22 August 2016, \
Here, the transition from 2D to 3D crystals has been analysed for finite temperature and for T=0 including quantum fluctuations.\
\
4. Section V. \
The authors refer to the instability linear-zigzag in a 1D chain referring to an experimental analysis of the Los Alamos group, which studied small ion chains and hinted towars critical behaviour based on the numerical work of J. Schiffer, Phys. Rev. Lett. 70, 818 (1993). I point out that the full analysis of the critical behaviour has been performed in \
S. Fishman et al, Phys. Rev. B 77, 064111 - Published 25 February 2008.\
and confirmed in several experiments by the groups of T. Sch\uc0\u228 tz, T. Mehlstaeubler, and F. Schimdt-Kaler.\
